            <scopecontent id="aspace_590f459888216398f76a9e71e728213c">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series III. Rev. John Curry Gay Gift contains writings, letters, and other material. The series features numerous drafts, holograph and typescript, to poems discarded by Stevens while renting an apartment from David Tait Gay and Teresa Curry Gay on 735 Farmington Avenue in West Hartford. Most of the poems found here were published in <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                     <part>Harmonium</part>
                  </title> (New York: Alfred A. Knopf, 1923).</p>
            </scopecontent>
            <acqinfo id="aspace_f71b4ab78eb892e86c5b1c4bc2ba5267">
               <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
               <p>Gift of Rev. John Curry Gay, 1974.</p>
            </acqinfo>
